The paper deals with data structures for planar embeddings of graphs, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). The UP-tree is a new data structure, which is likely to be of interest to researchers in data structures (cs.DS). The paper also involves combinatorial algorithms for solving the upward planar embedding extension problem, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper may also be of interest to researchers in graph theory (cs.GT) and computational topology (cs.DL) due to the use of the SPQR-tree and its extension to the UP-tree.
